{"article_id":"BNZjdwnnHdMBESID","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Alabama sent the most restrictive abortion bill in the country to the governor 's desk Tuesday night ,","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"with the state 's Senate passing legislation","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"that could punish doctors","depth":12},{"id":4,"text":"who perform abortions","depth":12},{"id":5,"text":"with life in prison .","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"The state 's Republican backers have pushed the legislation ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"which amounts to a near-total ban on abortion in the state ,","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"forward with the express goal","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"of overturning Roe v. Wade , the Supreme Court case","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"legalizing abortion .","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"Alabama lawmakers join legislators in several other states","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"in putting forth legislation","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"to restrict abortion , such as Georgia 's recent fetal heartbeat bill","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"After more than four hours of debate , the Republican-led Senate voted 25-6 to pass HB 314 ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"which would slap doctors with up to 99 years in prison","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"for performing an abortion .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"The Alabama House passed the bill earlier this month .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"The law only allows exceptions","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"`` to avoid a serious health risk to the unborn child 's mother , ''","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"for ectopic pregnancy","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"and if the `` unborn child has a lethal anomaly . ''","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"Democrats re-introduced an amendment","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"to exempt rape and incest victims ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"but the motion failed on an 11-21 vote .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Republican Gov . Kay Ivey will have six days","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"to sign the legislation ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"though the bill would not take effect until six months after becoming law .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"Ivey has not publicly taken a stance on the bill","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"but has previously aligned herself as anti-abortion ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"lamenting the courts","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"striking down another Alabama abortion law last year","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"`` As this legislation is still making its way through the legislative process ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"the governor intends to withhold comment","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"until it makes its way to her desk for signature , ''","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Ivey spokeswoman Lori Jhons said in a statement .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"American Civil Rights Union of Alabama Executive Director Randall Marshall said","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"that his organization would join with the national ACLU , Planned Parenthood , and Planned Parenthood of Southeast","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"to challenge the bill in court within `` a few weeks ''","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"should it become law .","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"The bill 's consideration Tuesday made frequent reference to the chamber 's dramatic vote last week","depth":5},{"id":41,"text":"to drop an amendment","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"that would have made exemptions to abortions","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"performed for instances of rape or incest .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Republican State Sen. Clyde Chambliss ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"who ushered the bill through the chamber ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"emphasized in his introduction","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that the bill impacts women","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"who are `` known to be pregnant ''","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"and would provide `` every female","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"that 's pregnant","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"or thinks","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"they 're pregnant ,","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"and the male","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"who was involved ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"it gives them that window of time","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"-- this bill does not change that window of time . ''","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"In a news release , Chambliss touted","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"that his bill outlaws surgical abortions","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"as soon as a pregnancy can be medically determined .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"Speaking on the Senate floor ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Chambliss repeatedly referred to a `` window '' of time between conception and when a woman knows for certain","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"that she 's pregnant .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"The state senator said","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"he believed","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that time was between about seven and 10 days .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"`` She has to take a pregnancy test ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"she has to do something","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"to know","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"whether she 's pregnant or not , ''","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"`` You ca n't know that immediately ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"it takes some time for all those chromosomes and all that . ''","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"Many women do n't yet know for certain","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"that they 're pregnant even at six weeks into a pregnancy","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"-- the earliest","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"a fetal heartbeat can be detected .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"When Democratic state Sen. Rodger Smitherman asked","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"what would happen under the bill to a young girl","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"who was a victim of incest","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"and found out","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"she was pregnant ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"Chambliss said","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"that he hoped","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"that the bill would result in young women","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"learning to seek physical and mental help quickly","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"if they are abused .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"`` What I hope is ,","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"if we pass this bill ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"that all young ladies would be educated by their parents , their guardians","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"should a situation like this occur ,","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"you need to go get help","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"-- you need to do it immediately , ''","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"Chambliss said .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"For more on reproductive rights","depth":4},{"id":96,"text":"On this week 's episode of `` United Shades of America , '' W. Kamau Bell visits Jackson , Mississippi","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"to explore the divisive world of reproductive rights and reproductive justice","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"including abortion , sex education and women 's health .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"Tune in on Sunday at 10 p.m. ET/PT .","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"`` Then also they can get justice in the situation , ''","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"he added .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"`` If they wait ,","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"justice delayed","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"is justice denied . ''","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Democratic state Sen. Vivian Figures told Chambliss","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"that a rape victim 's trauma `` is not your business . ''","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"`` You do n't have to raise that child ,","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"you do n't have to carry that child ,","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"you do n't have to provide for that child ,","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"you do n't have to do anything for that child , ''","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"she told Chambliss .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"`` But yet you want to make that decision for that woman ,","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"that that 's what she has to do . ''","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"Figures proposed amendments","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"to have legislators","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"who backed the bill","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"pay for the anticipated legal fees","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"accrued by subsequent legal challenges ,","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"to expand Medicaid in anticipation of the bill 's impact on low-income women ,","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"and to make having a vasectomy a class A felony ,","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"as the bill would designate performing an abortion .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"All three motions failed .","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"Eric Johnston , head of the Alabama Pro-life Coalition and the drafter of the initial legislation , told CNN","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"while the amendment","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"to exempt rape and incest victims","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"is `` sympathetic ''","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"and `` deals with very difficult issues , ''","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"it would upend the law 's legal standing .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"`` Regardless of how the conception takes place ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"the product is a child ,","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"and so we 're saying","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"that that unborn child is a person","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"entitled to protection of law , ''","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"he added .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"`` So if , be it a rape or incest conception ,","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"then it would be impossible to ask a judge","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"which of these is protected by law","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"and which is not . ''","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"Staci Fox , president of Planned Parenthood Southeast , told CNN before the chamber 's vote","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"that `` even the authors of this bill know","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"that it is blatantly unconstitutional","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"and would n't stand up in court . ''","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"`` We 've seen the continual chipping away year after year in Alabama","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"and efforts get bolder and bolder each year , ''","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"Fox said .","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"`` I think","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"with the President and now Kavanaugh on the court , the politics in Alabama just feel emboldened to take this egregious swipe at women 's health care . ''","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"But in the larger legal landscape , Marshall cast doubt","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"on whether this bill would ever take on Roe ,","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"citing how the case would take several years to get to the Supreme Court","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"while several other states have already passed so-called heartbeat bills","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"effectively banning abortion .","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"`` There are already 14 cases nationwide in the pipeline ,","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"two of which are currently at the Supreme Court of the United States , ''","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"`` The notion","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"that somehow this is going to be the vehicle","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"for the Supreme Court to reconsider Roe v. Wade","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"is really misplaced . ''","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":321,"left":0,"right":320,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":320,"left":254,"right":319,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":199,"right":253,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":195,"right":198,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":195,"left":184,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":173,"right":183,"relation":"elaboration","nu